OL,6,FResponding to the First Minister,
OL,7,Fshadow Scottish secretary Ian Murray
OL,8,Fclaimed tackling child poverty was "in
OL,9,Fthe Labour Party's DNA".
OL,11,FThe Scottish Government regularly
OL,12,Fcites its actions to help struggling
OL,13,Ffamilies, in particular pointing to
OL,14,Fthe much-lauded Scottish child payment
OL,15,F` a #26.50 per week per child payment
OL,16,Ffor families already receiving
OL,17,Fbenefits as part of the devolved
OL,18,Fsocial security system north of the
OL,19,Fborder.
