OL,3,CSwinney urges 'Westminster reset' on
OL,4,Cchild poverty action
OL,6,F"The Labour Party must finally commit
OL,7,Fto scrapping the hated two-child limit
OL,8,Fand other Westminster policies that
OL,9,Fstand in the way of Scotland's own
OL,10,Fprogress on eradicating child poverty.
OL,12,F"Uniting with a common purpose to
OL,13,Feradicate child poverty is possible `
OL,14,Fand I urge the Labour leader to commit
OL,15,Fhimself to that goal."
OL,17,FMr Murray said: "The last Labour
OL,18,Fgovernment lifted thousands of
OL,19,FScottish children out of poverty and
OL,20,Fan incoming Labour government is
OL,21,Fcommitted to tackling child poverty.
